cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a correspondence between their model and a fragment of the contract logic PCL. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with detecting obligations of each participant, which can be seen as a problem in AI. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as contracts often involve sensitive information and security is an important aspect of contract enforcement. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new model for contracts, which can be seen as a programming language for contracts. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper deals with resolving circular dependencies among contract clauses, which is a common problem in software engineering.
